2. String Input & Methods
python


name = input("Enter your name: ")
print(f"Hello, {name.title()}!")
print(f"Uppercase: {name.upper()}")
print(f"Lowercase: {name.lower()}")
print(f"Length: {len(name)}")
print(f"Replaced 'a' with '@': {name.replace('a', '@')}")



         output:
             Hello, Alice!
            Uppercase: ALICE
             Lowercase: alice
              Length: 5
            Replaced 'a' with '@': @lice

3. String Slicing & Formatting
python

text = "Python is awesome!"

# Slicing
print(f"First 6 chars: {text[:6]}")
print(f"Last 8 chars: {text[-8:]}")
print(f"Reverse: {text[::-1]}")
print(f"Every 2nd char: {text[::2]}")

# f-string formatting
name, age = "Bob", 25
print(f"{name} is {age} years old")
Output:


Copy code
First 6 chars: Python
Last 8 chars: awesome!
Reverse: !emosewa si nohtyP
Every 2nd char: Pto s wsm!
Bob is 25 years old
4. String Reverse
